verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Command the children of Israel, and say unto them, My offering, and my bread for my sacrifices made by fire, for a sweet savour unto me, shall ye observe to offer unto me in their due season.
verses.verse_html:
2Command the children of Israel, and say unto them, My offering, and my bread for my sacrifices made by fire, for a sweet savour unto me, shall ye observe to offer unto me in their due season. ▼
▼ a sweet…: Heb. a savour of my rest

tokens.text: for my sacrifices made by fire
unto me in their due season

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a sweet…: Heb. a savour of my rest
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a sweet…: Heb. a savour of my rest

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt say unto them, This is the offering made by fire which ye shall offer unto the Lord; two lambs of the first year without spot day by day, for a continual burnt offering.
verses.verse_html:
3And thou shalt say unto them, This is the offering made by fire which ye shall offer unto the Lord; two lambs of the first year without spot day by day, for a continual burnt offering. ▼
▼ day by day: Heb. in a day

footnotes.body_text: ▼ day by day: Heb. in a day
footnotes.body_html: ▼ day by day: Heb. in a day

verses.text_plain: The one lamb shalt thou offer in the morning, and the other lamb shalt thou offer at even;
verses.verse_html:
4The one lamb shalt thou offer in the morning, and the other lamb shalt thou offer at even; ▼
▼ at even: Heb. between the two evenings

footnotes.body_text: ▼ at even: Heb. between the two evenings
footnotes.body_html: ▼ at even: Heb. between the two evenings

verses.text_plain: And a tenth part of an ephah of flour for a meat offering, mingled with the fourth part of an hin of beaten oil.
verses.verse_html: 5And a tenth part of an ephah of flour for a meat offering, mingled with the fourth part of an hin of beaten oil.

verses.text_plain: It is a continual burnt offering, which was ordained in mount Sinai for a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 6It is a continual burnt offering, which was ordained in mount Sinai for a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the drink offering thereof shall be the fourth part of an hin for the one lamb: in the holy place shalt thou cause the strong wine to be poured unto the Lord for a drink offering.
verses.verse_html: 7And the drink offering thereof shall be the fourth part of an hin for the one lamb: in the holy place shalt thou cause the strong wine to be poured unto the Lord for a drink offering.

tokens.text: shalt thou cause the strong wine

verses.text_plain: And the other lamb shalt thou offer at even: as the meat offering of the morning, and as the drink offering thereof, thou shalt offer it, a sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 8And the other lamb shalt thou offer at even: as the meat offering of the morning, and as the drink offering thereof, thou shalt offer it, a sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And on the sabbath day two lambs of the first year without spot, and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and the drink offering thereof:
verses.verse_html: 9And on the sabbath day two lambs of the first year without spot, and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and the drink offering thereof:

verses.text_plain: This is the burnt offering of every sabbath, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
verses.verse_html: 10This is the burnt offering of every sabbath, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.

verses.text_plain: And in the beginnings of your months ye shall offer a burnt offering unto the Lord; two young bullocks, and one ram, seven lambs of the first year without spot;
verses.verse_html: 11And in the beginnings of your months ye shall offer a burnt offering unto the Lord; two young bullocks, and one ram, seven lambs of the first year without spot;

verses.text_plain: And three tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one bullock; and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one ram;
verses.verse_html: 12And three tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one bullock; and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, for one ram;

verses.text_plain: And a several tenth deal of flour mingled with oil for a meat offering unto one lamb; for a burnt offering of a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 13And a several tenth deal of flour mingled with oil for a meat offering unto one lamb; for a burnt offering of a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And their drink offerings shall be half an hin of wine unto a bullock, and the third part of an hin unto a ram, and a fourth part of an hin unto a lamb: this is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.
verses.verse_html: 14And their drink offerings shall be half an hin of wine unto a bullock, and the third part of an hin unto a ram, and a fourth part of an hin unto a lamb: this is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.

verses.text_plain: And one kid of the goats for a sin offering unto the Lord shall be offered, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
verses.verse_html: 15And one kid of the goats for a sin offering unto the Lord shall be offered, beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.

verses.text_plain: And in the fourteenth day of the first month is the passover of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16And in the fourteenth day of the first month is the passover of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And in the fifteenth day of this month is the feast: seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.
verses.verse_html: 17And in the fifteenth day of this month is the feast: seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.

verses.text_plain: In the first day shall be an holy convocation; ye shall do no manner of servile work therein:
verses.verse_html: 18In the first day shall be an holy convocation; ye shall do no manner of servile work therein:

verses.text_plain: But ye shall offer a sacrifice made by fire for a burnt offering unto the Lord; two young bullocks, and one ram, and seven lambs of the first year: they shall be unto you without blemish:
verses.verse_html: 19But ye shall offer a sacrifice made by fire for a burnt offering unto the Lord; two young bullocks, and one ram, and seven lambs of the first year: they shall be unto you without blemish:

tokens.text: they shall be unto you without blemish

verses.text_plain: And their meat offering shall be of flour mingled with oil: three tenth deals shall ye offer for a bullock, and two tenth deals for a ram;
verses.verse_html: 20And their meat offering shall be of flour mingled with oil: three tenth deals shall ye offer for a bullock, and two tenth deals for a ram;

verses.text_plain: A several tenth deal shalt thou offer for every lamb, throughout the seven lambs:
verses.verse_html: 21A several tenth deal shalt thou offer for every lamb, throughout the seven lambs:

verses.text_plain: And one goat for a sin offering, to make an atonement for you.
verses.verse_html: 22And one goat for a sin offering, to make an atonement for you.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall offer these beside the burnt offering in the morning, which is for a continual burnt offering.
verses.verse_html: 23Ye shall offer these beside the burnt offering in the morning, which is for a continual burnt offering.

verses.text_plain: After this manner ye shall offer daily, throughout the seven days, the meat of the sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the Lord: it shall be offered beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.
verses.verse_html: 24After this manner ye shall offer daily, throughout the seven days, the meat of the sacrifice made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the Lord: it shall be offered beside the continual burnt offering, and his drink offering.

tokens.text: After this manner ye shall offer
of the sacrifice made by fire

verses.text_plain: And on the seventh day ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work.
verses.verse_html: 25And on the seventh day ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work.

verses.text_plain: Also in the day of the firstfruits, when ye bring a new meat offering unto the Lord, after your weeks be out, ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work:
verses.verse_html: 26Also in the day of the firstfruits, when ye bring a new meat offering unto the Lord, after your weeks be out, ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work:

verses.text_plain: But ye shall offer the burnt offering for a sweet savour unto the Lord; two young bullocks, one ram, seven lambs of the first year;
verses.verse_html: 27But ye shall offer the burnt offering for a sweet savour unto the Lord; two young bullocks, one ram, seven lambs of the first year;

verses.text_plain: And their meat offering of flour mingled with oil, three tenth deals unto one bullock, two tenth deals unto one ram,
verses.verse_html: 28And their meat offering of flour mingled with oil, three tenth deals unto one bullock, two tenth deals unto one ram,

verses.text_plain: A several tenth deal unto one lamb, throughout the seven lambs;
verses.verse_html: 29A several tenth deal unto one lamb, throughout the seven lambs;

verses.text_plain: And one kid of the goats, to make an atonement for you.
verses.verse_html: 30And one kid of the goats, to make an atonement for you.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall offer them beside the continual burnt offering, and his meat offering, (they shall be unto you without blemish) and their drink offerings.
verses.verse_html: 31Ye shall offer them beside the continual burnt offering, and his meat offering, (they shall be unto you without blemish) and their drink offerings.

tokens.text: they shall be unto you without blemish
